Gnathotectum, chelicerae, and subcapitular structures as in female. Cheliceral shaft, excluding basal section, 80 – 86 long; movable digit 24 – 28 long, bidentate; fixed digit with offset subapical tooth and short file of two or three fine teeth. Relative lengths of subcapitular setae as in adult (
